Zhiyang Ong is a recent CS Ph.D. dropout from the University of Verona. He received his BS EE with honors from the University of Adelaide and the MS EE degree from the University of Southern California (USC).

He has interned with the Institute of Microelectronics and the Bioinformatics Institute in Singapore, where he was involved in system administration and biomedical imaging research. He was also: a software quality assurance intern with the Macintosh team of Symantec Corporation in Santa Monica, CA; a resident advisor at USC's Parkside International Residential College; and a research intern at the Department of Information Engineering and Computer Science, University of Trento, in Italy. His research interests include electronic design automation (EDA), complex systems, and model order reduction.

He is currently developing EDA software for his EDA start-up that would sell EDA software to engineers involved in heterogeneous integrated circuit design and verification. He has designed several integrated circuits, including pipelined processors, and developed several EDA software. He is primarily a C++ developer on UNIX-like platforms, but is a semi-Rubyist/Pythonista and Lua/Clojure hacking wannbe.

He is a member of ACM and SIGDA, and IEEE and 3 IEEE societies. In addition, he has participated in different SIGDA or IEEE CEDA events for students, such as SIGDA Design Automation Summer School and ICCAD CADathlon. He ran cross country for both of his alma maters, and outdoor track for Adelaide.
